bug.short_desc: Wi-Fi password dialog has two different background colours
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1166151 Screenshot
Description of problem: When connecting to a Wi-Fi, the window asking for the password has a different colour around the password text field, than the rest of the window.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): cinnamon-3.0.4-1.fc24.x86_64 cinnamon-menus-3.0.2-1.fc24.x86_64 cinnamon-desktop-3.0.2-1.fc24.x86_64
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Try to connect to a password protected Wi-Fi 2. The window asking for the password appears.
Actual results: The colour around the password text field is different than the rest of the window. See attached screenshot.
Expected results: The background colour of the whole window should be the same.
I haven't updated my notebook to f24 yet, only my mainbox with a network wire , so i can't test it for the moment. A screenshot about and which theme you are use would be helpful yet.

Created attachment 1166236 Themes
(In reply to Wolfgang Ulbrich from comment #1) > A screenshot about and which theme you are use would be helpful yet.
There's already a screenshot attached to the BZ showing the problem.
About the theme: I think everything is still on its default. Which information exactly do you need and where do I find it? I attached a screenshot from the "Themes" window in Cinnamon. Does it answer your question?

Ok, thanks for reporting that. It is BlueMenta theme which is the default in Cinnmon or Mate. Not sure if this dialog is from gnome-polkit or Network-Manager-applet. Anyway, i will fix it if i've have updated my notebook. I needed to rewrite every theme complete for gtk+-3.20 ......and i missed that application :)
